cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.DS, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a variation of the λ-calculus, which is a fundamental concept in logic and computation. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the Resource λ-calculus is a model for programming languages. 
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses a strictly typed restriction of the Resource λ-calculus. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the ability to count addends in normal forms. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a possibility as the Resource λ-calculus is a model for formal languages.
